               <placeName>Däbrä Mäʿar Qəddəst Maryam</placeName>
               <placeName type="alt">Məʿərafä Qəddusan Qəddəst Maryam</placeName>
               <country>Ethiopia</country>
               <region>Təgray</region>
               <settlement from="2010-12-03" to="2010-12-03">wäräda Ganta ʾAfäšum, ṭabiya Ḥadənnät, qušät Däbrä Mäʿar</settlement>
               <location>
                  <geo>14.186783 39.39175</geo>
                  <height unit="m">2594.0</height>
               </location>
               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" notBefore="1600" notAfter="1700">1600-1700</date>
                  <desc type="foundation"/>
                  <ab type="history">Gädam. The monastic community declined. Only one monk (a native of Goğğam) was residing at the upper church in 2010). &#xD;
The site accomodates two churches: the upper (2665 m ASL), smaller and older church is dedicated to St. Gäbrä Mänfäs Qəddus (called ʿOna Maʿṣo); the church below (Däbrä Mäʿar), big and recent, is dedicated to  St. Mary.&#xD;
Tabots (at least 3): Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus, Mary, Zärʾa Buruk (possibly a few more).</ab>
                  <ab type="description">19 Mss. photographed: <ref target="ESmqm001">MQM-001</ref> "Miracles of Mary"; <ref target="ESmqm002">MQM-002</ref> "Four Gospels"; <ref target="ESmqm003">MQM-003</ref> "Vita of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus"; <ref target="ESmqm004">MQM-004</ref> "Synaxarion (March)"; <ref target="ESmqm005">MQM-005</ref> "Missal"; <ref target="ESmqm006">MQM-006</ref> "The Book of the Funeral Rite"; <ref target="ESmqm007">MQM-007</ref> "Missal"; <ref target="ESmqm008">MQM-008</ref> "Vita of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus"; <ref target="ESmqm009">MQM-009</ref> "Psalter"; <ref target="ESmqm010">MQM-010</ref> "The Rite of the Holy Week"; <ref target="ESmqm011">MQM-011</ref> "The Book of the Chants"; <ref target="ESmqm012">MQM-012</ref> "Book of  ʾAsläṭi"; <ref target="ESmqm013">MQM-013</ref> "Epistles of Peter"; <ref target="ESmqm014">MQM-014</ref> "Missal"; <ref target="ESmqm015">MQM-015</ref> "Homily of the Trinity"; <ref target="ESmqm016">MQM-016</ref> "Homily of St. Michael"; <ref target="ESmqm017">MQM-017</ref> "Vita of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus"; <ref target="ESmqm018">MQM-018</ref> "The Book of the Chants"; <ref target="ESmqm019">MQM-019</ref> "Book of  ʾAsläṭi"</ab>
